< Text>
OMGosh. The chicken tacos at this place are amazing, and possibly the best I've ever had. I was staying at Hotel Soltaire, and it was a 20 mins walk-- but, honestly worth it. I enjoyed walking through the surrounding community. The people, the music, the smells (or food), and the culture. Glorious.</Text>

<time>1456461645351<//time><rating>4</rating>< review>
I'm giving this place 4 stars based on their food.
The only bad and worst thing about this place is their service (besides the place looking like a dump).  They could make so much more money and tips if they were on top of things.

THE PLUS....
This place has the best burritos, tortas and tacos ever.  I love the carne adasa here, they cook and marinate it to perfection.  They use the best bread to grill for the tortas.  Their rice and salsas are also at the top of the list.  I highly recommend just going to the window and ordering something easy and quick.</review>

< Rating>
5</Rating>
<Review>Hard to see from street, even though it is right on the street with outside seating.  Located next to Crest Theater, which is much more visible.

Beautiful expression of the owner's soul. All the murals were created by the owner.  Every piece and placement discovered, to include the fountain, was created in the owner's mind and with his hands.  A lovely person to talk with if you visit while he is there.  Walking around throughout the cafe, is in part like walking around inside the mind of the owner.

The motif of food and surroundings is Mediterranean. Outside seating has both views of the sidewalk/street and of the Crest Theater Garden.

Near K street and 11th; 2 blocks from the state Capitol Building.

Both outside tables and inside seating are available.

keywords: Middle East restaurant, Persian, delicious, fine dining, good restaurant, artistic, lunch, dinner

I'm not affiliated with restaurant in any way, but if you enjoy a restaurant I think it deserves detailed support.
Guidepost.us<//Review>< pictures>

<Date>1564368421659< /Date><Rating>5<//Rating>< GmapID>
0x809ad129bc57cdd9:0xb1a15ccca3062591< /GmapID>
<UserId.>112688313270209604848<//UserId.><Resp>None<//Resp>< Review>
I have been craving this place once a week ever since my indian and Afghan friends introduce me to this place.
.
I like coming here for the lunch buffet. They have amazing samosa which is this fried pastry with stuffed potatoes and peas inside and is not oily but so flavorful. I love to dip it in the white sauce which you need to request. This alone keeps me coming to the buffet once or twice a week.
.
I also love their white basmati rice which is fluffy and they mix in some corn peas and carrots which is very colorful and taste is simple and settled..
.
Also I love their simple salad which is salad and the white sauce for dip.
.
As well I love their veggie of the day which changes and sometimes it could cauliflower broccoli eggplant  cabbage or something. But yes simple buffet which is great for vegetarians which i am not but my co workers are but i love the vegeterian options so i have no problem.
.
They do offer 2 option meats like chicken which is cooked kind of like tikka masala with jalapeno but it's not tikka masala sauce. As well they have this lamb beef meat ball dish which the flavor is ok.
.
Also each buffet comes with a soda and their soda is the healthy not name brand sodas which is made out of real sugar and etc.
.
Also I tried their fries with white sauce which they ran out of samosa and omg it was so good that they do sell it on the side as an order and it's amazing if I'm not doing buffet.
.
All their food is consistent and taste the same even if they are busy. The food price is reasonable too. Yes its busy during lunch so come early ;)<//Review>

< Review>
Not horrible, but not great. A couple of the owners are funny and friendly.

Prices are not listed on A LOT of the items, so my daughter and I get to the counter with two bottles of soda and a bag of chips and the total comes to $10. Overpriced but they get away with it because the store is close to a lot of apartments and easy for people to walk to it.

Basically, It's an okay place for an occasional snack or to pick up milk or water really quick, but for extended shopping needs, go somewhere else. .<//Review>

Dr. Steensma, OD is very knowledgeable about vision and the care and health of the eye. He goes out of his way to explain everything clearly and calmly during appointments and he answered all of my questions. I never felt rushed. <Rate>5<//Rate>< Review>
I have always received the best and most professional care with Dr. Steensma. But my latest experience has been the best by far. Some time back he told me that I should get cataract surgery. He did my exam, worked up the report and referred me to a well-known eye surgeon, who, by the way performed surgery on him. I had both eyes done(one a day ago)and had lenses implanted since I had been legally blind all my life. Today, at my one day follow-up. I tested out at 20/25. Talk about a miracle! And Dr.Steensma is such a professional that he is the follow-up person after the surgery. I could not ask for a more competent and highly skilled professional than Dr. Steensma. You don't need to shop around. I did that years ago but found the best right here in Port Hueneme. I had considered going to USC which has a new state of the art program which my colleague, who teaches in the School of Medicine at USC, recommended. But I trusted Dr. Steensma and I was correct. The whole staff is exceedingly helpful and caring. I have never had to wait long since the appointments, unlike many other offices many have experienced, does not have a waiting room stacked with people. This great place gets 5 stars only because there is no 6th star!!< /Review>

<gmapID>0x80e84e13185cbd8b:0xee2a817ed4b6249e< /gmapID><Rate>5<//Rate><name>Geydi Valenzuela</name><resp>None</resp><pictures>None</pictures><user>113855869943630789040<//user>< time>

< review>
**From my Yelp Review**

Who knew learning about the health of your peepers could be fun?

Dr. Steensma reminds me of Dr. Oz; they make learning about your health exciting. He exudes genuine passion about his profession as well as shows true concern for your eye health.

If you can, get the CT scan for your eyes (about $30 I believe).
It was so much fun to see my eyeballs, haha. It's neat to actually see all the veins and arteries that connect to it in a 3D-like format. Thanks to all the machines and technology that was used, I feel at peace about the health of my eyes.

I didn't end up buying contacts since unfortunately my eyes are extremely dry at the moment (we're working on it) so I can't comment on the brands they offer or their prices. The glasses though, are on point. They offer the ever classic Ray Bans, Kate Spade, Coach and more! Their prices are fair and the lens warranty is even better, two years if I recall correctly? (dont quote me) I believe they also advised that if my lenses were to get scratched within the first year they could smoth the scratches out for me.

The service I received from Dr. Steensma and the lovely ladies that make up his staff was amazing; they are ready to answer any question you may have. I had a lot of fun (and no shame) taking selfies with some of the frames. The girl that assisted me (forgot to ask her name- Ooops!) was so patient and took out more frames for me to look at. Even though I took a while looking over their frame selection, I never felt pressured into buying them. In fact, Dr. Steenma had his staff correct my worn-out, low quality frames (bought them online for pennies- you get what you pay for) out of courtesy. No strings attached. That's quality service for ya!

Tip: They are ALWAYS booked so schedule in your appointment ahead of time. Totally worth the wait.

Ps I went to see another 'popular' Optometrist in the Ventura area prior to coming here and their service was very poor. Close to terrible actually.<//review>

<Review>My favorite place for poke bowls. I was very happy they opened one near my home! I like that they have a lot of options. Prior to COVID, they had a self serve topping area, but now the workers put it on for you. It's still great and they are very generous with the toppings. I'm sure you can get more if you wanted to. My favorites are the furikake, garlic chips and onion chips. They have a lot of different types of "mix-ins" for your poke bowl, but you have to choose between different things or its an extra charge. There's seaweed salad or avocado, spicy crab mix or regular crab mix, corn or edamame, pineapple or mango. There might be some other choices. I'll definitely be back to satisfy my next poke bowl craving.</Review>< pics>

< text>
Growing up, La Bodeguita was AWESOME but I don't know what is going on as of late. I've gone a couple of times in the past 6 months just because, and every time there are homeless people harassing you outside or following you in the store. Prices aren't as cheap as you'd think. Cashiers are as friendly as ever. Meat department has a lot of flies. Gave it 2 stars because the staff is nice. But it honestly does not look as clean as it used to. Also, double check expiration dates, I almost bought an expired juice bottle.</text>

<name>Colette</name><Time>1562442419484<//Time><rating>3< /rating>< Text>
I haven't been to Red Lobster in a while but this past trip was disappointing. I loved the calamari before and enjoyed the broccoli pieces that went with the calamari (it no longer comes with the plate; it only comes with bell peppers). I ordered it anyway. The calamari arrived and was heavily breaded. It was very disappointing. The picture is of us after eating some of it (you receive more than what's shown). It used to be one of my favorite places to get calamari. I will no longer order it from Red Lobster. The broccoli now is served as a separate appetizer and it was tasty but it only came with 4 pieces of broccoli for the entire appetizer plate. The steak and sides were fine. I feel like it was any old ordinary steak. Perhaps this location isn't as great as the one I frequently visited (Oceanside, CA) but I definitely don't see myself craving Red Lobster that badly to travel 25 min to get to. I just remember it being better...< /Text>

4 1/2 Stars Very good service!

This visit was much better than our last 2017 visit (see my 2017 review at bottom).

This New England style restaurant is very nice (It does remind me of New England visits). It is very clean like every restaurant in New England; the interior is warm, welcoming; very relaxing. I really like the wall themed paintings, the Lighthouse photos and nautical decorations throughout. Good interior colors also!

Once again the service was very good. I talked with several friendly diners and they gave rave reviews on their dining experiences at this Red Lobster. Everyone I asked loved it. One group said they had visited the night before and they really love Red Lobster.

Our visit was enjoyable. Our server (Jeremy) gets a top rating. We all ordered different dinners and all were happy with our selections. The Cheddar Bay Biscuits are delicious. I loved the Asparagus (slightly charred, great texture and very juicy). My Salad and Ranch Dressing were both okay; I liked the variety of greens. I had Stuffed Talapia (their Cajun Spice is very good).. the Talapia was juicy but I have had much better and I wasn't impressed with the stuffing. I also had a side of Mashed Potatoes with a gravy and small bits of lobster (the three flavors don't work well together..  I wouldn't order this one again).

The rest of the party ordered Steak and Lobster.  The plating looked great. One Steak was a bit bland and other was tasty (we think it is because the tastier Steak was ordered with the Lobster on the side, but don't really know why one Steak tasted much better than other.

My review went up from 3 Stars last year to 4 1/2 Stars today. Jeremy gets 5 Stars (we gave him good tip to thank him for his special service).

We are visiting this Red Lobster at least once a year.

Last years review  was 3 Stars and 4 Stars for service:

(2017),

Service here was very good (if I was evaluating on service they would get 4 plus).. The food was not impressive. Several items that they served were bland and not very well presented. They need a new cook at this restaurant. We have gone to this restaurant over the years but I fail to be impressed even one time (the rest of the family has no complaints).

Note: This Red Lobster is very close to the 5 Freeway, Disneyland, many major hotels, a hundred restaurants and shopping of every kind... Very good location if you are visiting.< /Text><rating>4</rating>< gmap_id>

<Text>$$$

4 1/2 Stars Very good service!

This visit was much better than our last 2017 visit (see my 2017 review at bottom).

This New England style restaurant is very nice (It does remind me of New England visits). It is very clean like every restaurant in New England; the interior is warm, welcoming; very relaxing. I really like the wall themed paintings, the Lighthouse photos and nautical decorations throughout. Good interior colors also!

Once again the service was very good. I talked with several friendly diners and they gave rave reviews on their dining experiences at this Red Lobster. Everyone I asked loved it. One group said they had visited the night before and they really love Red Lobster.

Our visit was enjoyable. Our server (Jeremy) gets a top rating. We all ordered different dinners and all were happy with our selections. The Cheddar Bay Biscuits are delicious. I loved the Asparagus (slightly charred, great texture and very juicy). My Salad and Ranch Dressing were both okay; I liked the variety of greens. I had Stuffed Talapia (their Cajun Spice is very good).. the Talapia was juicy but I have had much better and I wasn't impressed with the stuffing. I also had a side of Mashed Potatoes with a gravy and small bits of lobster (the three flavors don't work well together..  I wouldn't order this one again).

The rest of the party ordered Steak and Lobster.  The plating looked great. One Steak was a bit bland and other was tasty (we think it is because the tastier Steak was ordered with the Lobster on the side, but don't really know why one Steak tasted much better than other.

My review went up from 3 Stars last year to 4 1/2 Stars today. Jeremy gets 5 Stars (we gave him good tip to thank him for his special service).

We are visiting this Red Lobster at least once a year.

Last years review  was 3 Stars and 4 Stars for service:

(2017),

Service here was very good (if I was evaluating on service they would get 4 plus).. The food was not impressive. Several items that they served were bland and not very well presented. They need a new cook at this restaurant. We have gone to this restaurant over the years but I fail to be impressed even one time (the rest of the family has no complaints).

Note: This Red Lobster is very close to the 5 Freeway, Disneyland, many major hotels, a hundred restaurants and shopping of every kind... Very good location if you are visiting.< /Text><Pictures>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMq6ty40xZPPa50-dK48VrpQaHXXQipi4Wlug8T=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipN0VhZKV0zGwGFj6wKGLQOHR77axmmZgsxe1aAK=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipP48bXYxqoL7k8sG5ql2Co5Od8W99Nwqr5MsISt=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNZhz_wtZBVlNl3gpSrg9zgc4Bf5MOPk_sENTS5=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMEU-WfXgOX1AVoTJiVuIDzF43z_6q9YEzeU-GM=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNcgeYDUQCD_e4mDtX3oGvmpXMt6hP4cx6eaW79=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipOWjKwWNlsZNIxJj1XwSTdEqaidjEh2Yqrcyizp=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipM_SL3-hUx2FGl5Fae-V7_4dyMCSrAfm-XmNoOi=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNPL1FeaL7A4XcHgYJhozHppF7u0A6xvs-yTJ-7=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMVng3oVEOE6R1z-xJOAznF6VKCDL1TvqFBcuor=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMSshNZYBmdYhNpCwXjN_csW0Xw6YQ_r_HRRHLz=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPY9oUA_h6cRSpGyN28C14UOHMr5rK2DWnVJ4G9=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]< /Pictures><resp>None</resp><Gmap_id>0x80dcd803b70fbf43:0x57807dd9fe03a9cc<//Gmap_id></record>

Great food as usual. It was my birthday and I have the red lobster app (which is free and you get rewards!!)  So this time I got a choice of 2 different appetizers (both with lobster) or any dessert on the menu!! Nice choices. I had the crab legs, they were very good. <Pics>None<//Pics><rate>4<//rate><Date>1555194777660</Date>< review>
We came in a Saturday afternoon, there was plenty of parking, but lot needed restriping.   The restaurant was clean, but was a bit dated.

We were greeted and seated immediately and the waitress took our drink orders quickly.

We ordered and received our food quickly.  The biscuits were amazing and all you can eat.  I had a steak, mashed potatoes and green beans, and my wife had lobster and asparagus. It was all very good.   We paid via the table top device which we definitely appreciated not having to rely on the wait staff.

The waitress was efficient and friendly, but did seem a bit disinterested.  On our way out we walked by the manager who was reviewing something with an employee and they failed to acknowledge us.

I would have given five stars if the waitress and manager had been a bit more engaging.< /review>

< Review>
The decor is nice and the staff are friendly. It didn't take that long to get our food either. I liked a couple of the items I ordered, the tomato mozzarella caprese and the tortilla with dip. Unfortunately, I thought the main was less pleasant. The shrimp was either too salty or bland and the lobster was also way too salty. I thought the steak was just barely average.
You probably won't leave thinking it was money well spent if you value food over friendly staff. If you think friendly staff > food, it might be worth for you.< /Review>

The good:
Waitstaff (Jenise) was great!

<Rating>1</Rating>< Review>
What follows is a very negative experience I had at the Garden Grove Red Lobster. But I‚Äôm updating my review to reflect the way management handled the situation. After emailing them a copy of my review, they contacted me later that day and expressed their extreme displeasure at their employees. They assured me they would look into it, and made the gesture of offering me a full refund for the meal. I feel this went above and beyond in handling the situation, and showed me they actually care about the people they serve in their restaurant. I look forward to the improvements they will make in the future.

We walked out of here after dinner saying to ourselves, ‚ÄúThat was the worst dining experience we‚Äôve ever had.‚Äù

We normally don‚Äôt frequent chain restaurants, but decided to give it a shot for dinner. This was my first time ever at a Red Lobster. It will absolutely be my last time. It takes a lot for me to drop it to a one star review. This Red Lobster earned every bit of it.

To start, the service was bizarre. Our server came to our table very energetically, almost jittery, talking extremely fast and going on and on about menu items. Once he finally left, we all commented on how strange his behavior was. As the evening went on, it became more and more apparent that he was on something. He became even more awkward and started sweating profusely. He blabbered on and on about trying to get our order in on the computer, apologized for ‚Äúbeing so weird,‚Äù and exclaimed, ‚ÄúSweet, we‚Äôre making tons of money off you guys!‚Äù This was after 2 of us declined more shrimp for the Endless Shrimp meal. It nearly ruined the meal.

What actually ruined the meal was the food. My wife ordered lobster. For the price, it should have been cooked to perfection. Instead it was tough, chewy and overcooked. The shrimp was bland. The fries soggy. The only thing worth eating were the biscuits.

The orders were put in wrong. I ordered linguine and scampi shrimp with mashed potatoes. I got breaded shrimp and fries. Napkins were never delivered when requested. At one point, a random order of coconut shrimp showed up that nobody ordered. After a brief confrontation between our server and the guy with the coconut shrimp, they decided to just give it to us. When we asked for a to go bag (for the biscuits only), it never came. We had to get it from the hostess, who seemed perturbed to be doing that for us.

And to top it all off, they have managed to work a technology scam into their pricing. When we sat down, we noticed a small device, like and iPad. Thought maybe it was an ordering device? My 9 year old daughter picked it up and said it had some games. As kids will do, she started playing something, but not for long because my wife and I agreed that it‚Äôs pretty ridiculous to have games provided for a family dinner. So we removed it from our table. When we got the bill, we found a ‚Äúgame‚Äù charge for $1.99. Turns out, they charge for those games. Nothing on the table to declare that. When I later inspected one of these devices, the first thing that pops up is a game to play (targeting children). When you click on it, a big green button comes up, saying something like ‚ÄúPlay Unlimited Access.‚Äù In tiny print below that, which no child would (or could) read, it gives the price of $1.99. Unreal. Is Red Lobster owned by a vaping company? They seem to both target children in unethical ways.

Never again will I go to a Red Lobster. Our meal was over $100, and I‚Äôm so mad at myself for being duped so bad.< /Review>

Wasn't happy with our experience at all. We originally were gonna go to joes crab Shack but they were packed. We went to red loster thinking oh its nicer and more mellow and won't be a hectic atmosphere. Well I was wrong. We got there, seated quite quickly. My family and I ordered. My daughter got the sirloin, we asked for medium/well and got rare. My green beans didn't come out with my food, my fiances baked potatoe was hard on the outside and inside. It was odd because our waitress went missing and we were wondering where she went, a lady came to our table and said she had an asthma attack and she will be helping us out. She had seen we were out of our drinks and got us new ones. A guy came and did the same but we told him we got our drinks and that we just needed a new potatoe and green beans weren't given, he said he'd be right back and never did. We called a host to our table because no one came back for sometime and I told him about my daughters steak and he said he'd call someone, well no one ever came. Our waitress came back finally and I told her about everything and by the time she brought green beans, they were cold. She said they must have forgotten to come out with the food and we told her to just take my daughters meal off the bill because we were already done with ours.
